\begin_inset Formula $3$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $4$
\end_inset

 and so on.
 It is a remarkable fact that any function that is sufficiently differentiable
 can (locally) be approximated arbitrarily well by polynomials:
\end_layout

